casebody.data:
No. 1828. Hayne v. Irvine,

November Term, 1885.

March 1, 1886.

Opinion by

Mr. Justice McGowan,

This was a controversy without action, involving the construction of a will, originally submitted to this court for adjudication. The court held that they had no original jurisdiction of the matter, and ordered the case to be stricken from the docket without prejudice.
